PN,42502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F425A1773090365
OL,3,CMan found guilty of rape and knowingly
OL,4,Cinfecting seven men with HIV
OL,6,FHall became aware he had HIV when he
OL,7,Fwas diagnosed in 2010. He was advised
OL,8,Fby medical professionals repeatedly
OL,9,Fabout the importance of taking anti-
OL,10,Fretroviral medication, which prevents
OL,11,Fthe transmission of the deisease to
OL,12,Fsexual partners.
OL,14,FMore than 95% of people in the UK who
OL,15,Fhave HIV take the medication, which
OL,16,Freduces the amount of the virus in the
OL,17,Fblood to undetectable levels.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,426,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F425A1773090365
OL,3,CMan found guilty of rape and knowingly
OL,4,Cinfecting seven men with HIV
OL,6,FHowever, in 2016, it became clear that
OL,7,FHall had not been following the
OL,8,Ftreatment as the levels of HIV in his
OL,9,Fblood were detectable at infectious
OL,10,Flevels.
OL,12,FHe went on to have unprotected sex
OL,13,Fwith his victims between November 2016
OL,14,Fand May 2023, in several instances
OL,15,Fagainst their will.
OL,17,FThe court heard how he had failed to
OL,18,Fdisclose his HIV status and his
OL,19,Fvictims only found out when they
OL,20,Fthemselves tested positive with the
OL,21,Fdisease.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,426,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F425A1773090365
OL,3,CMan found guilty of rape and knowingly
OL,4,Cinfecting seven men with HIV
OL,6,FIn her prosecution opening speech in
OL,7,FNovember, Kama Melly KC said: "The
OL,8,Fdefendant knew from being repeatedly
OL,9,Ftold about the risks of what he was
OL,10,Fdoing, if he did not keep to the
OL,11,Fmedication, if he did not stick to his
OL,12,Ftreatment regime, and continued
OL,13,Ffinding, repeatedly, young and often
OL,14,Fvulnerable males for sexual activity."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
